  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (fidelity gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a simplified single-phase Newtonian blood formulation; non-Newtonian shear-thinning behaviour and turbulence-induced stress fluctuations are present in the physical system but are excluded from the model. No fidelity trade study documenting the impact of these exclusions has been performed.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-ident",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-cpb-hemolysis-credibility",
