      "rationale": "Steady-state incompressible Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes equations solved with multiple reference frame approach for impeller rotation. Hemolysis predicted via power-law stress-exposure model (Giersiepen et al.). Model form documented in simulation plan. Blood rheology represented as Newtonian fluid with constant viscosity — a simplification noted in the simulation plan as an accepted modelling choice. Non-Newtonian shear-thinning behaviour and turbulence-driven stress fluctuations, which are present in the physical system, are excluded from the model form. No fidelity trade study quantifying the effect of these exclusions on RHI prediction has been performed. Gradation 2 requirement considered met based on documentation of assumptions alone."
